You are a strict quality judge evaluating DIY home repair QA items.

Evaluate whether every tip in the "tips" field provides non-obvious, task-specific advice that adds value beyond what is already covered in the "steps" field.

FAIL if:
- Any tip merely restates a step from the "steps" field without adding new insight or a reason why
- Any tip offers generic encouragement or advice that applies to all repairs ("measure twice, cut once", "take your time", "ask for help if needed")
- Any tip is so obvious that a first-time homeowner would already know it without being told
- The tips as a whole do not help the homeowner avoid a specific failure mode or achieve a better result for this particular repair

PASS if:
- Every tip provides specific, non-obvious guidance that is distinct from the steps
- Tips help the homeowner avoid common mistakes, improve quality, or save time in ways specific to this repair

Respond with exactly one word: PASS or FAIL.
